[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m138[0m[39m:     * The maximum number of cell styles in a .xls workbook.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m139[0m[39m:     * The [0m[32m'official'[0m[39m limit is [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m, but POI allows a slightly larger number.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m140[0m[39m:     * This extra delta takes into account built-in styles that are [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mautomatically[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m141[0m[39m:     * <p>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m142[0m[39m:     * See [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m143[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview and Root-Cause Analysis  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The Jazzer fuzz log shows only class‐instrumentation messages and no parsing [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic is ever exercised: the fuzzer loads and rewrites hundreds of POI classes, but[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediately returns from its entry point—most likely because POI’s built‐in [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“DoS‐guards” [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmax record length, max image length, max record count[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m detect [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munrecognized or malformed inputs early, throw exceptions, and the harness silently [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mswallows them.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By default, HSSFWorkbook caps BIFF record lengths at [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m [0m[1;36m000[0m[39m bytes, images at [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m50[0m[39m [0m[1;36m000[0m[39m [0m[1;36m000[0m[39m bytes, and the RecordFactory caps the total number of records at [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmillion. These limits fire quickly on fuzz inputs, short‐circuiting deep parsing [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand preventing any crash or unexpected behavior from being discovered.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - To preserve existing functionality for production users while allowing the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz harness to traverse deeper BIFF parsing logic, we should introduce an opt‐in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverride mechanism for these internal limits—leveraging the existing [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mIOUtils.getByteArrayMaxOverride[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` API—so that under fuzzing [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor any test harness [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat sets the override[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, all caps effectively become “unlimited,” forcing HSSF to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparse the entire stream and thus enabling coverage of parser logic.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patches to Implement  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Modify [0m[1;35mHSSFWorkbook.getMaxRecordLength[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Replace the simple static return of `MAX_RECORD_LENGTH` with logic that [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks `[0m[1;35mIOUtils.getByteArrayMaxOverride[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. If the override is ≥ [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, use it; [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39motherwise, fall back to the existing limit.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – This mirrors the existing pattern in `[0m[1;35mgetMaxImageLength[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Update RecordInputStream [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand any other internal parser[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to use the new [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mgetMaxRecordLength[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method rather than the raw `MAX_RECORD_LENGTH` field.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Ensures that parser buffers and chunk reads honor the override.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Adapt [0m[1;35mRecordFactory.createRecords[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to use [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mIOUtils.getByteArrayMaxOverride[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` as the effective max record count.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Compute `int effectiveMaxRecords = override ≥ [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m ? override : [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX_NUMBER_OF_RECORDS;` and pass that into [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mIOUtils.safelyAllocateCheck[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mrecords.size[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, effectiveMaxRecords[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – No new APIs are needed; reusing `[0m[1;35mIOUtils.getByteArrayMaxOverride[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` avoids [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintroducing a second override mechanism.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   D. Documentation [0m[35m/[0m[39m Comments  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – In Javadoc for `setMaxRecordLength`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`getMaxRecordLength`, note that [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz‐mode can override via the existing `poi.io.max.byteArraySize` system property [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor corresponding environment variable.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Step-by-Step Implementation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. In `HSSFWorkbook.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround lines [0m[1;36m220[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m240[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – Change  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        public static int [0m[1;35mgetMaxRecordLength[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            return MAX_RECORD_LENGTH;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        to  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        public static int [0m[1;35mgetMaxRecordLength[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            int override = [0m[1;35mIOUtils.getByteArrayMaxOverride[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            return override >= [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m ? [0m[1;35mMath.min[0m[1;39m([0m[39mMAX_RECORD_LENGTH, override[0m[1;39m)[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                : MAX_RECORD_LENGTH;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. In `RecordInputStream.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39msearch for references to `MAX_RECORD_LENGTH`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – Replace direct field references [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`HSSFWorkbook.MAX_RECORD_LENGTH`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalls to `[0m[1;35mHSSFWorkbook.getMaxRecordLength[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – This ensures that when reading multi‐byte record payloads, the override is [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrespected.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. In `RecordFactory.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m180[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m195[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – Compute the effective max record count before the loop:  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        int override = [0m[1;35mIOUtils.getByteArrayMaxOverride[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        int effectiveMaxRecords = override >= [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m ? override : MAX_NUMBER_OF_RECORDS;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – Then change the allocation‐check call:  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mIOUtils.safelyAllocateCheck[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mrecords.size[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, effectiveMaxRecords[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Verify that no existing unit tests set `poi.io.max.byteArraySize`; this patch[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mleaves default behavior unchanged [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlimit = [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m [0m[1;36m000[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m [0m[1;36m000[0m[39m [0m[1;36m000[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for everyone else. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. In project documentation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mCHANGELOG or javadoc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, mention that the existing [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIOUtils override mechanism now also controls HSSF record limits to enable fuzzing [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor customized max‐size scenarios.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification & Preservation of Logic  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Production behavior is unaltered: default caps still apply unless someone [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexplicitly sets the override [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich only tests or advanced users do[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzz harness can now set the single environment variable or system property [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat `[0m[1;35mIOUtils.getByteArrayMaxOverride[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` already checks [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`-Dpoi.io.max.[0m[33mbyteArraySize[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m1000000000[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to remove parsing guards and drive deep [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBIFF logic.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No harness code, test code, or external dependencies are modified—only POI’s [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mown parsing limits are made “fuzz‐overrideable.”  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This promotes full exercise of parser code under fuzzing, increasing the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchance of uncovering real vulnerabilities.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If any side‐effect arises [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., OOM on enormous inputs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, it will manifest [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munder fuzz isolation; production users are unaffected unless they explicitly [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverride.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential Side‐Effects & Mitigations  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Very large buffers or record counts could cause OOM during fuzz runs. [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMitigation: the fuzzer runs in a sandbox with limited heap, so any OOM is caught by[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibFuzzer as a “crash,” which is actually beneficial to highlight resource [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexhaustion.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No broad exception catching is introduced; parsing errors still throw the same[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexceptions, only the early truncation is lifted.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing unit and integration tests continue to pass under default limits.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. References to Similar Patterns  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mHSSFWorkbook.getMaxImageLength[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` already defers to [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mIOUtils.getByteArrayMaxOverride[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No additional override methods needed; reusing [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mIOUtils.getByteArrayMaxOverride[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` follows the established POI pattern.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA patch was attempted in the Apache POI `RecordInputStream` class to add a [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheader‐size check and safe buffer allocation. After applying the patch, the build [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfailed with hundreds of “illegal start of expression” and related syntax errors in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`RecordInputStream.java`, indicating that the patch corrupted the file’s [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructure—likely by misplacing or removing braces or comment delimiters around [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethods and Javadoc.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`POIHSSFFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m exercised Apache POI’s HSSF record parsing. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No runtime crash or exception from the original run was shown; the issue context [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfocuses solely on introducing a size check for BIFF records.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `RecordInputStream.java`, the patch replaced the existing code around line [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m137[0m[39m:  [0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Removed a call to `[0m[1;35mreadNextSid[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Inserted logic to read a [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte header [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mreadFully[0m[1;39m([0m[39mheader[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, extract `sid` and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`size`, compare `size` against `[0m[1;35mHSSFWorkbook.getMaxRecordLength[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, throw [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`RecordFormatException` if too large, and allocate `data` with [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mIOUtils.safelyAllocate[0m[1;39m([0m[39msize, maxLen[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch also altered fields `_dataInput` initialization to wrap a new [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`LittleEndianInput`.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- On compilation, the Java compiler emitted syntax errors starting at the Javadoc [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmarker “* @see #[0m[1;35mremaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m”.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Errors include “illegal start of expression”, unexpected `#`, missing semicolons,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand cascading errors in every method declaration.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This indicates that the patch disrupted the class’s brace structure or comment [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msyntax, so the compiler no longer recognizes method boundaries or Javadoc blocks.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mObservations & Findings  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The first reported syntax error is at the Javadoc line preceding `public int [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, suggesting the patch accidentally removed or misordered a closing `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor `*[0m[35m/[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Subsequent errors on every method imply the parser thinks it is still inside an [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvalid block.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch diff does not show explicit changes to Javadoc comments, but the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontext lines [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`*[0m[35m/[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m may have shifted.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The exact location of brace insertion/removal around the constructor or static [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minitializer in `RecordInputStream.java`.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Proper placement of the new code block—verify opening and closing braces so that[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe constructor ends cleanly before Javadoc.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Alignment of Javadoc comment delimiters [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/[0m[39m** … *[0m[35m/[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and the following method [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msignature.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m203[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[39m*[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m204[0m[39m:        * How to recognise end of stream?[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m205[0m[39m:        * In the best case, the underlying input stream [0m[1;39m([0m[39min[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ends just after [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe last EOF record[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m206[0m[39m:        * Usually however, the stream is padded with an arbitrary byte count.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mExcel and most apps[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m207[0m[39m:        * reliably use zeros for padding and if this were always the case, this[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode could just[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m208[0m[39m:        * skip all the [0m[1;39m([0m[39mzero sized[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m records with [0m[33msid[0m[39m==[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m.  However, bug [0m[1;36m46987[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshows a file with[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m209[0m[39m:        * non-zero padding that is read OK by Excel [0m[1;39m([0m[39mExcel also fixes the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpadding[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m210[0m[39m:        *[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m211[0m[39m:        * So to properly detect the workbook end of stream, this code has to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentify the last[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m212[0m[39m:        * EOF record.  This is not so easy because the worbook bof+eof pair do [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot bracket the[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m213[0m[39m:        * whole stream.  The worksheets follow the workbook, but it is not easy[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto tell how many[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m214[0m[39m:        * sheet sub-streams should be present.  Hence we are looking for an EOF[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrecord that is not[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m215[0m[39m:        * immediately followed by a BOF record.  One extra complication is that[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbof+eof sub-[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m216[0m[39m:        * streams can be nested within worksheet streams and it's not clear in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthese cases what[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m217[0m[39m:        * record might follow any EOF record.  So we also need to keep track of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe bof/eof[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m218[0m[39m:        * nesting level.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m219[0m[39m:        *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mkey, int initialOffset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws RecordFormatException` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m140[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a. After setting `_dataInput` and `_bhi`, insert a block to:  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • Allocate a [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m‐byte header array  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • Read exactly [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes into it [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia the `readFully` utility[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • Extract `sid` and `size` with `[0m[1;35mLittleEndian.readUShort[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • Compare `size` against `[0m[1;35mHSSFWorkbook.getMaxRecordLength[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • If excessive, throw `RecordFormatException`  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • Otherwise allocate `byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m data = [0m[1;35mIOUtils.safelyAllocate[0m[1;39m([0m[39msize, maxLen[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • Reassign `_dataInput` to a new `LittleEndianInput` over `new [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mByteArrayInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b. After this block, restore the original line `_nextSid = [0m[1;35mreadNextSid[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` so [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat the constructor finishes initializing the first record SID.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure all braces introduced by this `if`[0m[35m/[0m[95mblock[0m[39m are balanced, and that no `[0m[35m/[0m[39m* [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [33m...[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m[39m` comment markers are lost or shifted.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Add necessary imports [0m[1;39m([0m[39mif not already present[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `import java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;`  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `import org.apache.poi.util.IOUtils;`  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `import org.apache.poi.util.LittleEndian;`  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `import org.apache.poi.hssf.usermodel.HSSFWorkbook;`  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `import org.apache.poi.util.RecordFormatException;`  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Verify Javadoc and comments remain intact  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm the Javadoc before `public int [0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` remains delimited by `[0m[35m/[0m[39m** [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [33m...[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m[39m` and no lines from the constructor leak into it.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run `mvn compile` to ensure that only the intended logic changed and that no [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msyntax errors remain.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This strategy directly addresses the root cause: an unbalanced or missing [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructor brace and/or comment delimiter corrupted the class’s syntax.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- By restoring the constructor’s closing `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` and Javadoc delimiters, the compiler [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcan once again recognize method boundaries.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Re‐inserting the size‐check logic inside the constructor [0m[1;39m([0m[39mrather than overwriting[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe brace[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m preserves existing functionality: the first SID is still read via [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mreadNextSid[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, and we validate and safely allocate the first record’s buffer.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Using the same pattern as in `RecordFactoryInputStream` ensures consistency: read[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheader, validate size, use `[0m[1;35mIOUtils.safelyAllocate[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Potential side effects are minimized: all new code lives inside the constructor, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoes not alter fuzzing or harness logic, and does not affect any other methods or [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtests.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This keeps existing Javadoc, utility methods, and class invariants intact.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After these changes, rerun existing tests to confirm no regressions.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [33m...[0m[39m [0m[1;39m[[0m[39mTRUNCATED[0m[1;39m][0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn Apache POI fuzzing run using a custom harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`POIHSSFFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m revealed no [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediate crashes but served as context for a proposed patch. The patch rewrote [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparts of `RecordInputStream` to add explicit header parsing, size validation [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39magainst `[0m[1;35mHSSFWorkbook.getMaxRecordLength[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, and safe buffer allocation via [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mIOUtils.safelyAllocate[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. It also removed the class’s `[0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` override [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand replaced raw stream handling with `LittleEndianInputStream`. After applying the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch, the project failed to compile. Hundreds of errors appeared across [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`RecordInputStream` and dozens of POI classes that depended on the removed methods,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmissing imports, mismatched API calls, and unimplemented interface methods.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue [0m[1;39m([0m[39mHarness Output[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The log shows a libFuzzer-based harness instrumenting hundreds of POI classes [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand running a single input [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m times.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No exceptions or crashes appear; instrumentation messages fill the log.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This output establishes that the fuzzer entry point is `POIHSSFFuzzer` and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat code under test is the HSSF [0m[1;39m([0m[39mBIFF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m record parsing layer.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - File modified: [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/record/RecordInputStream.java`[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Removals:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `import java.io.IOException;`[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `import java.util.Locale;`  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `import org.apache.commons.io.output.UnsynchronizedByteArrayOutputStream;`  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `import org.apache.poi.hssf.record.crypto.Biff8DecryptingStream;`  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Additions:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `import java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;`  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `import org.apache.poi.util.LittleEndian;`  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `import org.apache.poi.util.LittleEndianInputStream;`  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `import org.apache.poi.util.RecordFormatException;`  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • A block that reads four header bytes, parses `sid` and `size`, checks `size [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<= maxLen`, allocates `byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m data` via `[0m[1;35mIOUtils.safelyAllocate[0m[1;39m([0m[39msize, maxLen[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreads into `data`, and wraps it in a `LittleEndianInputStream`.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The class’s `[0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` override was deleted [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe patch removed the method [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstub and related Javadoc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Some existing code was reordered or refactored, but the bulk of record-reading[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic stayed intact.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Post-Patch Build Result[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `:poi:compileJava` task failed with ~[0m[1;36m35[0m[39m errors and ~[0m[1;36m11[0m[39m warnings.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Key error categories:[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `RecordInputStream` no longer implements `[0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` but still implements [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`LittleEndianInput`, which defines an abstract `[0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Numerous classes [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`FormatRecord`, `ExtSSTRecord`, `NameRecord`, [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`DimensionsRecord`, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m call `[0m[1;35mris.available[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or `[0m[1;35min.available[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`; those calls [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnow fail because `[0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` was removed.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • References to `IOException`, `Locale`, `Biff8DecryptingStream`, and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`UnsynchronizedByteArrayOutputStream` are now unresolved.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • API misuse: `[0m[1;35mLittleEndian.readUShort[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, int[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` does not [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexist—`[0m[1;35mLittleEndian.readUShort[0m[1;39m([0m[39mInputStream[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is expected, leading to signature [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmismatches.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - RecordInputStream interface conformance:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Reconcile removal of `[0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with `LittleEndianInput`. Determine [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhether `[0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` should be re-added or the interface changed.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Downstream dependencies:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Audit all `org.apache.poi.hssf.record.*` classes that invoke `[0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mreadAllContinuedRemainder[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, or rely on `Biff8DecryptingStream`.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Import consistency:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto read the stream[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpoi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/util/IOUtils.jav[0m[1;92ma:148[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m156[0m                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m148[0m[39m:    public static byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m [0m[1;35mpeekFirstNBytes[0m[1;39m([0m[39mInputStream stream, int limit[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws [0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m155[0m[39m:            int readBytes = [0m[1;35mbos.size[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m156[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreadBytes == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Revert unsafe/removal changes in RecordInputStream, restore interface [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconformance and dependencies  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Re-add the imports for java.io.IOException, java.util.Locale,  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     org.apache.commons.io.output.UnsynchronizedByteArrayOutputStream, and  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     org.apache.poi.hssf.record.crypto.Biff8DecryptingStream.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Re-insert the public int [0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdelegating to [0m[1;35mremaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msatisfy LittleEndianInput and all downstream [0m[1;35mris.available[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m calls.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Correct manual header‐parsing code to use the existing LittleEndian API  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Replace calls to [0m[1;35mLittleEndian.readUShort[0m[1;39m([0m[39mheader, off[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mLittleEndian.getUShort[0m[1;39m([0m[39mheader, off[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor [0m[1;35mLittleEndian.getShort[0m[1;39m([0m[39mheader,off[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m&[0m[1;36m0xFFFF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmatching the utility’s actual signatures.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Ensure header byte reads use [0m[1;35mRecordInputStream.readFully[0m[1;39m([0m[39mheader[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which is [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLittleEndianInput‐aware and respects decryption, instead of raw InputStream.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Keep safe‐allocation logic via IOUtils.safelyAllocate but place it in the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorrect location  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Immediately after parsing the two‐byte size field from the header, fetch int [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaxLen = [0m[1;35mHSSFWorkbook.getMaxRecordLength[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • If [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize > maxLen[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, throw new RecordFormatException with a descriptive message.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Allocate byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m data = [0m[1;35mIOUtils.safelyAllocate[0m[1;39m([0m[39msize, maxLen[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Call [0m[1;35mreadFully[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to pull in the record payload.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Wrap the record payload in a LittleEndianInputStream for consistent parsing  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Set _dataInput = new [0m[1;35mLittleEndianInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnew [0m[1;35mByteArrayInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Then call _nextSid = [0m[1;35mreadNextSid[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to position for the next record header, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreserving the existing record‐chaining logic.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Audit and restore downstream reference expectations  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Re-import java.util.Locale to support [0m[1;35mtoUpperCase[0m[1;39m([0m[39mLocale.ROOT[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLeftoverDataException [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand similar code[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Re-import Biff8DecryptingStream so [0m[1;35misCurrentRecordEncrypted[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and encryption [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths compile.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Re-import UnsynchronizedByteArrayOutputStream so [0m[1;35mreadAllContinuedRemainder[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand [0m[1;35mpeekFirstNBytes[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m continue working.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Verify LittleEndianInput implementation completeness  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Run a grep for any missing interface methods in RecordInputStream; ensure [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mreadByte[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mreadUByte[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mreadShort[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mreadUShort[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mreadInt[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mreadLong[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mreadDouble[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mreadFully[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mreadFully[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m,int,int[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mreadPlain[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m,int,int[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are all implemented or delegated.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Rebuild and clean up  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Compile the poi module, fix any residual missing‐symbol errors [0m[1;39m([0m[39musually missing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimports or signature mismatches[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Run existing unit tests for HSSF records to ensure parsing correctness is [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreserved.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Smoke‐test POIHSSFFuzzer to confirm no regressions in fuzz coverage.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification:  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Restoring [0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and missing imports resolves the bulk of compilation errors[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39macross ~[0m[1;36m35[0m[39m errors.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Using LittleEndian.getUShort matches the actual API, eliminating the “cannot find[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msymbol” issues for [0m[1;35mreadUShort[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m,int[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Reinserting Biff8DecryptingStream and UnsynchronizedByteArrayOutputStream imports[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreserves existing multi‐chunk and encryption logic.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Placing size validation and IOUtils.safelyAllocate inside the established [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheader‐read path ensures safe buffer limits without rewriting the entire [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBiffHeaderInput machinery.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– This approach minimally disrupts existing RecordInputStream logic, maintains [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbackward‐compatible interfaces, and fully addresses the evaluation report’s root [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcauses [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmissing methods, bad imports, API misuse[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPotential side‐effects & mitigation:  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– The header‐parsing block must reside in the constructor before any record data is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconsumed; incorrect placement could alter record boundaries. Mitigate by reviewing [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode flow around readNextSid/readDataSize.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Throwing RecordFormatException on oversize will alter behavior for extremely [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlarge records; tests should cover such edge cases.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– No harness or fuzzing code is modified; fuzz inputs continue to drive [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRecordInputStream as before.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
