[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe project’s Apache POI module was exercised under a Jazzer/libFuzzer harness [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout apparent runtime errors. A proposed patch to `RecordInputStream.java` aimed[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add early header parsing with a size‐check against [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mHSSFWorkbook.getMaxRecordLength[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Override the `[0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, int, int[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method to traverse and skip over CONTINUE [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrecords.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Refactor `[0m[1;35mreadAllContinuedRemainder[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to aggregate payloads more robustly.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the Java compiler produced hundreds of syntax errors in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`RecordInputStream.java`, all indicating unexpected tokens [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., “`;` expected”, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“invalid method declaration”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m starting at the newly inserted `public int [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m b, int off, int len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` declaration.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A fuzzer invocation [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`run_fuzzer POIHSSFFuzzer …`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m logs extensive [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstrumentation of POI classes and commences a run on `[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - There is no immediate crash or exception reported by the harness; the log ends[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith instrumentation messages truncated.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The underlying impetus appears to be hardening `RecordInputStream` against [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moversized records and improving its handling of Excel “Continue” records.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Observations from the Initial Log  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Multiple POI and Log4j classes are instrumented by Jazzer.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No Java compile‐time or runtime errors appear before the patch.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The harness environment uses `LittleEndianInputStream`, `IOUtils`, and POI’s [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ContinueRecord` semantics.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Imports added at the top of `RecordInputStream.java`:  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `java.io.ByteArrayInputStream`  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `org.apache.poi.hssf.record.ContinueRecord`  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In the constructor, code inserted to read the first [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte header, extract [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`sid` and `size`, check size against `[0m[1;35mHSSFWorkbook.getMaxRecordLength[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minitialize `_dataInput` with only that record’s payload.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A new override for `public int [0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m b, int off, int len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` was added to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwalk through CONTINUE records when the current record is exhausted.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The deprecated `[0m[1;35mreadAllContinuedRemainder[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method was refactored to read the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremainder and all subsequent CONTINUE payloads into a [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`UnsynchronizedByteArrayOutputStream`.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Result & Compilation Errors  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The build fails in `poi:compileJava` with errors starting at the newly added [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`public int [0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m b, int off, int len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` around line [0m[1;36m340[0m[39m.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Typical errors include:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • “‘;’ expected” and “invalid method declaration; return type required” at the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`public int [0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` line.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Numerous “class, interface, or enum expected” errors for every subsequent [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclaration until the end of the file.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - These errors strongly suggest that the new method declarations and/or braces [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare misplaced—likely inserted inside another method or block, corrupting the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclass’s brace structure.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Bracket Matching in RecordInputStream.java**: Verify that all opening `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand closing `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` braces around the insertion point align the new methods at the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclass level, not nested within an existing method.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Insertion Context**: Check the patch’s hunk offsets—ensure the `[0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverride and other method definitions are placed immediately after the appropriate [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclass‐scope boundary.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Imports & Dependencies**: Confirm that `ContinueRecord` and other helpers [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39me.g., `IOUtils`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are available and correctly imported.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Method Signatures**: Ensure no conflict or missing interface implementation [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39me.g., is the class already implementing `InputStream` methods?[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that could [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvalidate overriding `[0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **File Encoding/Line Endings**: Look for stray control characters or [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindentation issues that might confuse the Java parser.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA close review of the class structure around line [0m[1;36m340[0m[39m is needed to restore [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msyntactic validity before further functional testing.[0m                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [33m...[0m[39m [0m[1;39m[[0m[39mTRUNCATED[0m[1;39m][0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe project’s Java fuzzing harness runs successfully and begins instrumenting [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnumerous POI classes. A patch was applied to `RecordInputStream.java` that:[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Removed the existing `[0m[1;35mreadString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mreadUnicodeLEString[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` methods.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Added an `@Override public int [0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m b, int off, int len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Updated `[0m[1;35mreadAllContinuedRemainder[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to read record payloads more directly.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the build of the `poi` module failed with a cascade of [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompilation errors [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m29[0m[39m in total[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in `RecordInputStream.java`, all indicating syntax[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproblems such as “`; expected`” and “illegal start of expression.” The errors [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msuggest the patch disrupted the class’s structure [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmissing or mis-placed braces, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincorrect method placement[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The OSS-Fuzz job for Apache POI invoked a Java fuzzer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`POIHSSFFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minteractive mode.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer startup logs show successful loading of Jazzer hooks and [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstrumentation of hundreds of POI classes and interfaces.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No runtime crashes or exceptions were reported prior to the patch attempt.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `RecordInputStream.java`, around line [0m[1;36m350[0m[39m, the existing zero-argument [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`public String [0m[1;35mreadString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and the helper `[0m[1;35mreadUnicodeLEString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` were [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentirely removed.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Immediately after the removal, a new override of `[0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, int, int[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` was [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minserted. This new method loops through “CONTINUE” record fragments, reads up to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`len` bytes, and returns the number of bytes read or –[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m when no data remain.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The deprecated method `[0m[1;35mreadAllContinuedRemainder[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` was rewritten to [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexplicitly call `[0m[1;35mreadFully[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` on the current record and all subsequent [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ContinueRecord` fragments.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - At various points, code indentation and line breaks around method declarations[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwere adjusted, including use of builder-style invocation for [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`UnsynchronizedByteArrayOutputStream`.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Result  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `poi:compileJava` task failed with [0m[1;36m29[0m[39m errors, all in [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`RecordInputStream.java`. Example errors include:  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • “`; expected`” at the `public int [0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m b, int off, int len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` line  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • “illegal start of expression” at subsequent method declarations [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`readCompressedUnicode`, `readStringCommon`, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • “reached end of file while parsing” indicating unbalanced braces  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The errors indicate that after the patch, the Java compiler no longer [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrecognized class-level method declarations correctly, likely due to a missing [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclosing brace or an extra brace in the edited region. [0m[3;35mNone[0m[39m of the downstream [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmodules compiled successfully, halting the overall build.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **RecordInputStream.java Structure**: Examine the brace and parenthesis [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbalance around the insertion point [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnear line [0m[1;36m350[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Ensure that each method is [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclosed properly and that the new `[0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` override is inserted within the class [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbut outside any other method bodies.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Imports and Class Context**: Verify that `ContinueRecord`, `[0m[1;35mnextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mremaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, and `[0m[1;35mreadFully[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` are in scope and that required imports [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.poi.hssf.record.ContinueRecord`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remain present.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Surrounding Methods**: Review the methods immediately before and after the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch to confirm no unintended deletions or shifts of code occurred—for example, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfirm the `[0m[1;35mreadString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` removal did not remove a closing brace for the preceding[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethod or class.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Build Configuration**: Although the errors are syntax-level, ensure the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuild environment is using an appropriate Java source level [0m[1;39m([0m[39mJava [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m or above[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat any annotation-processing or compatibility flags are compatible with the new [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverride signature.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo assumptions are made about the root cause beyond what the compiler output [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreveals. The focus should be on restoring valid Java syntax and class structure in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`RecordInputStream.java` before attempting to revalidate the fuzzer [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstrumentation.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Remove the incorrect `@Override` annotation from the newly inserted `[0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Reinsert the `public int [0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m b, int off, int len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method at exactly one[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclass‐scope level, directly after the closing brace of `[0m[1;35mreadFully[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Make sure the preceding method [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`readFully`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m has exactly one `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` closing it.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Open the new `[0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with a single `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` and close it with a matching `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore the next existing method declaration [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`readCompressedUnicode`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm no stray braces or indent misalignments remain.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Balanced-braces check on `[0m[1;35mreadAllContinuedRemainder[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After patching that method, ensure there is:[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • A matching `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` for the try-with-resources block.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • A matching `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` for the catch block.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • A final `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` for the method itself.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify that the next method [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mremaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m starts at the correct class-scope [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlevel.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Verify the class‐ending brace is still present at the very end of [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRecordInputStream.java.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Rebuild the poi module:[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm that all [0m[1;36m29[0m[39m syntax errors in RecordInputStream.java are gone.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure no other compilation errors have been introduced.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOptional, if true InputStream semantics are required[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Change the class declaration on line [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m from[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        `public final class RecordInputStream implements LittleEndianInput`[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      to[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        `public final class RecordInputStream extends InputStream implements [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLittleEndianInput`[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Keep the `@Override` on the multi-byte `[0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m,int,int[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Add a single-byte override:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        `@Override public int [0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m b = new byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m; [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mint n = [0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[39mb,[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; return [0m[33mn[0m[39m==[0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m ? [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m : [0m[1;39m([0m[39mb[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[39m&[0m[1;36m0xFF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWhy this works[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Restoring the original methods and braces rebalances the class so that new [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethods are correctly recognized at class scope.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Dropping the invalid `@Override` immediately removes the compiler complaints on [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `[0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` signature.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- By not touching any harness, test code, or external dependencies, we preserve [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting functionality and fuzzer entry points.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The optional extension to InputStream is a safe, backwards-compatible way to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlegitimately override `[0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` if downstream code ever treats RecordInputStream [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mas an InputStream.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mReferences[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The class signature at [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpoi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/record/RecordInputStream.jav[0m[1;92ma:40[0m[39m.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The `[0m[1;35mreadFully[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method ends at line [0m[1;36m350[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39msee code_snippets cell for [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontext[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The erroneous patch was at lines ~[0m[1;36m350[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m380[0m[39m; restoring and then carefully [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mre-inserting fixes the cascade of syntax errors.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
